  "title": "Darts and Diagnostics at 7th Heaven",
  "summary": "Inside the relocated club 7th Heaven, a converted warehouse on Nar Shaddaa, the intelligence team kills time over a dart game while maintaining their cover. The Quarren medic Druze, a drink or two in, muses about being called a 'spirit-animal' while the Mirialan pilot Wrexan nurses caf and the marine quartermaster Siarra keeps a wary watch on the crowded room's many exits. Their banter ranges over field medicine, improvised first aid, and the grisly realities of combat surgery, punctuated by Druze repeatedly stabbing himself with darts and Siarra deftly winning the betting game. Siarra warns Druze that desperate locals may forcibly 'acquire' anyone known to have medical skill, advising him to keep something sharp and lethal close and to shoot first. Out-thrown and out of credits, Druze pays his share and retires to his bunk, leaving the team's cover intact for the next phase of the operation.",
